    "content": "<p>A balanced Wheatsone bridge ABCD has the following arm resistances :</p>\n<p>R<sub>AB</sub> = 1 k$$\\Omega$$ $$\\pm$$ 2.1%; R<sub>BC</sub> = 100 $$\\Omega$$ $$\\pm$$ 0.5%; R<sub>CD</sub> is an unknown resistance; R<sub>DA</sub> = 300 $$\\Omega$$ $$\\pm$$ 0.4%. The value of R<sub>CD</sub> and its accuracy is</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "30 $$\\Omega$$ $$\\pm$$ 3 $$\\Omega$$"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "30 $$\\Omega$$ $$\\pm$$ 0.9 $$\\Omega$$"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "3000 $$\\Omega$$ $$\\pm$$ 90 $$\\Omega$$"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "3000 $$\\Omega$$ $$\\pm$$ 3 $$\\Omega$$"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "B"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Under balanced condition,</p>\n<p>$${R_{CD}} = {{{R_{BC}} \\times {R_{DA}}} \\over {{R_{AB}}}} = {{(100 \\pm 0.5\\% )(300 \\pm 0.4\\% )} \\over {(1000 \\pm 2.1\\% )}}$$</p>\n<p>$${R_{CD}} = {{100 \\times 300} \\over {1000}} + (0.5\\%  + 0.4\\%  + 2.1\\% )$$</p>\n<p>$${R_{CD}} = 30 \\pm 3\\% $$</p>\n<p>% Error = $$\\pm$$ 3%</p>\n<p>$${R_{CD}} = 30 \\pm 30 \\times {3 \\over {100}} = 30 \\pm 0.9\\,\\Omega $$</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2022,
    "yearKey": "gate-ee-2022",
    "difficulty": null
  },
